APPROVED STRONG ACTION VERBS
==================================================
Accomplishment: achieved, attained, completed, earned, exceeded, finished, won
Leadership/Initiative: chaired, coordinated, delegated, directed, executed, headed, orchestrated, organized, planned, produced, programmed, spearheaded
Creation/Building: architected, built, charted, created, designed, developed, devised, engineered, established, formalized, founded, implemented, incorporated, initiated, instituted, introduced, launched, pioneered
Improvement/Impact: accelerated, advanced, amplified, boosted, capitalized, conserved, consolidated, decreased, delivered, enhanced, enlarged, expanded, expedited, furthered, gained, generated, grew, improved, increased, lifted, maximized, outpaced, reconciled, reduced, saved, streamlined, upgraded
Communication/Collaboration: advised, briefed, campaigned, collaborated, composed, conveyed, drafted, edited, enlisted, explained, interpreted, persuaded, presented, promoted, publicized, recruited, translated

==================================================
WEAK VERBS TO AVOID
==================================================
helped, assisted, supported, facilitated, participated, responsible for, managed (unless leading people), oversaw, worked on, did, made, used, got, looked, took, kept, had, said, handled, led (unless directing a team)

Avoid vague or low-information verbs unless they are the most accurate wording for the role and context.

